==English==
{{wikipedia}}
=== Pronunciation ===
*{{IPA|/ˈzəʊdɪæk/}}
=== Etymology ===
{{Gr.}} [[ζωδιακός]], probably from [[ζωον]] "animal" and [[διακονός]] "servant, helper"

=== Noun ===
'''zodiac'''

#{{astronomy}}: A belt-like region in the sky that includes the apparent path of the sun, moon, and planets. It extends approximately eight [[degree]]s north and south of the [[ecliptic]].
#{{astrology}}: The twelve [[sign]]s, or [[house]]s, of the zodiac.
# A circle decorated with the signs of the zodiac.

